					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Element in heraldry</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"Lions passant" redirects here. For the flag used by <a href="/wiki/List_of_English_monarchs" title="List of English monarchs">English monarchs</a>, see <a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_England#Royal_banner_of_England" title="Coat of arms of England">Coat of arms of England §&#160;Royal banner of England</a>.</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"Lion Rampant" redirects here. For the flag used by <a href="/wiki/List_of_Scottish_monarchs" title="List of Scottish monarchs">Scottish monarchs</a> (and which now represents the <a href="/wiki/Monarchy_of_the_United_Kingdom" title="Monarchy of the United Kingdom">British monarchy</a> in <a href="/wiki/Scotland" title="Scotland">Scotland</a>), see <a href="/wiki/Royal_Banner_of_Scotland" title="Royal Banner of Scotland">Royal Banner of Scotland</a>. For the flag and arms used by the King of León, see <a href="/wiki/Heraldry_of_Le%C3%B3n" title="Heraldry of León">Heraldry of León</a>. For the game publishing company, see <a href="/wiki/Lion_Rampant_(game_publisher)" title="Lion Rampant (game publisher)">Lion Rampant (game publisher)</a>.</div>
