			<div class="thumb" style="width: 155px; height: 155px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Coat of arms of Bulgaria (1997, based on 19th-century coat of arms)"><img alt="Coat of arms of Bulgaria (1997, based on 19th-century coat of arms)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria.svg/125px-Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria.svg.png" decoding="async" width="125" height="105" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria.svg/188px-Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria.svg/250px-Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="810" data-file-height="679" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_Bulgaria" title="Coat of arms of Bulgaria">Coat of arms of Bulgaria</a> (1997, based on 19th-century coat of arms)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 160px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 155px; height: 155px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Greater_coat_of_arms_of_Georgia.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Coat of arms of Georgia (2004, based on 18th-century royal coats of arms)"><img alt="Coat of arms of Georgia (2004, based on 18th-century royal coats of arms)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Greater_coat_of_arms_of_Georgia.svg/125px-Greater_coat_of_arms_of_Georgia.svg.png" decoding="async" width="125" height="109" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Greater_coat_of_arms_of_Georgia.svg/188px-Greater_coat_of_arms_of_Georgia.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Greater_coat_of_arms_of_Georgia.svg/250px-Greater_coat_of_arms_of_Georgia.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="556" data-file-height="485" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_Georgia_(country)" class="mw-redirect" title="Coat of arms of Georgia (country)">Coat of arms of Georgia</a> (2004, based on 18th-century royal coats of arms)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 160px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 155px; height: 155px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Coat of arms of Latvia (1921)"><img alt="Coat of arms of Latvia (1921)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia.svg/125px-Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia.svg.png" decoding="async" width="125" height="99" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia.svg/188px-Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia.svg/250px-Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="780" data-file-height="620" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_Latvia" title="Coat of arms of Latvia">Coat of arms of Latvia</a> (1921)</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 160px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 155px; height: 155px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Coat_of_Arms_of_New_South_Wales.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Coat of arms of New South Wales"><img alt="Coat of arms of New South Wales" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Coat_of_Arms_of_New_South_Wales.svg/125px-Coat_of_Arms_of_New_South_Wales.svg.png" decoding="async" width="125" height="88" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Coat_of_Arms_of_New_South_Wales.svg/188px-Coat_of_Arms_of_New_South_Wales.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Coat_of_Arms_of_New_South_Wales.svg/250px-Coat_of_Arms_of_New_South_Wales.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="1050" data-file-height="743" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_New_South_Wales" title="Coat of arms of New South Wales">Coat of arms of New South Wales</a></div>
		</li>
</ul></div></div></div><p><b><big>Western depictions</big></b>
</p><p>Heraldic lions have also found their way onto municipal or county seals in the United States.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Eastern_depictions">Eastern depictions</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Lion_(heraldry)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Eastern depictions"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>Outside of classical heraldry, lions have also found their way onto the coats of arms or emblems used by modern states in Asia, often based on traditional depictions of lions in the respective cultures or regions.
</p>
<div class="mod-gallery mod-gallery-default mod-gallery-center"><div class="main"><div><ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional nochecker">
